\end{bmatrix}

sec.p:
For a Mat√©rn field with smoothness parameter 
uŒΩ, we need to work with Q^{
u+1}QŒΩ+1. We can efficiently compute the log-determinant, \log|Q^{
u+1}|log|QŒΩ+1|, and the quadratic form, x^T Q^{
u+1} xxTQŒΩ+1x, without explicitly forming Q^{
u+1}QŒΩ+1. To do this, we compute the Cholesky decomposition, Q = LL^TQ=LLT, where L is a lower triangular matrix, and make use of the following equations:

alternatives.tex-math:
\begin{aligned}
x^T Q x &= x^T L L^T x = ||L^T x||_2^2 \\
x^T Q^2 x &=  x^T L L^T L L^T x = ||LL^T x||_2^2 \\
x^T Q^3 x &=  x^T L L^T L L^T L L^T x = ||L^TLL^T x||_2^2.
\end{aligned}

